  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Synthetic adversarial sample targeting W-AR-05 (comparator absence) via D3 undercutting: the primary validation result omits the comparedAgainst link, while the comparator referenced in narrative text was derived from ventricular assist device (VAD) bench data rather than CPB operating conditions, creating an inference-method mismatch that is not flagged in the assessment.",
