      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis damage accumulation model selected with documented justification; sensitivity to model form alternatives reported.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on its established performance in rotating internal flow applications. The Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model (exponents α = 3.62×10⁻⁷, β = 2.416, γ = 0.785) was applied per published literature for centrifugal pump hemolysis CFD. A sensitivity study comparing Giersiepen versus Arora model parameters showed NIH variation of ±18%, which was documented as a model-form uncertainty contributor. Gradation 2 model form criterion satisfied."
    },
    {
