      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for fluid viscosity (±10%), impeller tip clearance (±0.05 mm), and inlet velocity profile (uniform vs. developed). NIH sensitivity to viscosity was 12% per 10% viscosity change; tip clearance sensitivity was 8% per 0.05 mm variation. Inlet profile had negligible effect (<2%) on predicted NIH. Input uncertainty ranges documented per manufacturer tolerance specifications. Gradation 2 model input criterion satisfied."
